This license applies to all parts of DMZ that are not externally
maintained libraries.

The externally maintained library sources included with DMZ are:

  - expat, located under foundation/3rdparty/expat. This code is copyright
    by the Expat maintainers and is released under an MIT license.

  - Lua, located under frameworks/lua/3rdparty/lua/base. This code is copyright
    by Lua.org and PUC-Rio and is released under an MIT license.

  - LuaJIT, located under frameworks/lua/3rdparty/lua/jit. This code is
    is a derived work from Lua and is copyright by Mike Pall.
    It is released under an MIT license.

  - HawkNL, located under frameworks/net/3rdparty/hawknl. This code is copyright
    by Phil Frisbie, Jr. and is released under the LGPL.
    see: http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/lgpl.html

External libraries used by frameworks in DMZ but not include with the source are:

  - Qt, This code is released under a LGLP/Commercial License.
    see: http://trolltech.com

  - OpenSceneGraph, This code is released under the OpenSceneGraph Public License
    (OSGPL) and is based on the Lesser Gnu Public License (LGPL).
    see: http://openscenegraph.org

  - Ogre3D, This code is released under the GNU Lesser Public License (LGPL).
    see: http://ogre3d.org

  - FMOD, This library is released under several licenses include a Free non-commercial
    licences.
    see: http://www.fmod.org/

